Introduction

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Base URL

http://api.memberz.test

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {token}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

You can retrieve your token by visiting your dashboard and clicking Generate API token.

Activity Logs

Get All

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/activity_logs/search" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/activity_logs/search"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/activity_logs/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Example response (401):

Show headers 
cache-control: no-cache, private
content-type: application/json
 

{
    "message": "Unauthenticated."
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

GET api/activity_logs/search

    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

fetch(url, {

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();

Auth

Reset Password

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/reset-password" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --data "{
    \"username\": \"john@mail.com\",
    \"token\": \"123010100101\",
    \"password\": \"mypassword02\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/reset-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

let body = {
    "username": "john@mail.com",
    "token": "123010100101",
    "password": "mypassword02"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/reset-password',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'username' => 'john@mail.com',
            'token' => '123010100101',
            'password' => 'mypassword02',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Example response (200):


{
    "message": "Password reset successful"
}

Example response (401):


{
    "message": "Error resetting password"
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST api/auth/reset-password

Body Parameters

username  string  

User email.

token  string  

Password Reset Token.

password  string  

New User Password.

Login

Get a JWT via given credentials.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --data "{
    \"username\": \"john@mail.com\",
    \"password\": \"mypassword01\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

let body = {
    "username": "john@mail.com",
    "password": "mypassword01"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/login',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'username' => 'john@mail.com',
            'password' => 'mypassword01',

    ]

$body = $response->getBody();

Request      

POST api/auth/login

Body Parameters

username  email  

User Email.

password  string  

User Password.

Logout

requires authentication

Log the user out (Invalidate the token).

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/logout" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/logout"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/logout',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

GET api/auth/me

Forgot Password

requires authentication

Send a reset password link to user email. This endpoint allows user to reset their forgotten password.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/forgot-password" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --data "{
    \"username\": \"john@mail.com\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/forgot-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

let body = {
    "username": "john@mail.com"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/forgot-password',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'username' => 'john@mail.com',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST api/auth/forgot-password

Body Parameters

username  email  

The email for the password reset link.

Register new user/member

requires authentication

This endpoint allows to create new user account.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/register" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --data "{
    \"first_name\": \"John\",
    \"last_name\": \"Ansah\",
    \"email\": \"john.ansah@mail.com\",
    \"gender\": \"male\",
    \"dob\": \"1980-01-03\",
    \"mobile_number\": \"+2332440000001\",
    \"password\": \"mypassword01\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/auth/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

let body = {
    "first_name": "John",
    "last_name": "Ansah",
    "email": "john.ansah@mail.com",
    "gender": "male",
    "dob": "1980-01-03",
    "mobile_number": "+2332440000001",

Request      

GET api/banks/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/banks/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=magni" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/banks/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "magni",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/banks/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'magni',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/contribution_receipts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=quia" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/contribution_receipts/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "quia",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/contribution_receipts/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'quia',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/contribution_types/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=ut" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/contribution_types/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "ut",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/contribution_types/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'ut',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/countries/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=et" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/countries/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "et",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/countries/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'et',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Request      

GET api/currencies/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/currencies/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=numquam" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/currencies/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "numquam",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/currencies/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'numquam',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4

GET api/event_attendees/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/event_attendees/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=ut" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

    "http://api.memberz.test/api/event_attendees/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "ut",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/event_reminder_broadcasts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=dolorum" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/event_reminder_broadcasts/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "dolorum",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/event_reminder_broadcasts/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'dolorum',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:

Request      

GET api/events/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/events/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=omnis" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/events/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "omnis",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/events/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'omnis',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Example response (401):

Show headers

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/events?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \

);

    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/member_accounts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=exercitationem" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/member_accounts/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "exercitationem",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/member_accounts/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'exercitationem',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Query Parameters

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/member_images/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=corporis" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/member_images/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "corporis",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/member_images/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'corporis',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

requires authentication

Example request:

    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --form "member_id=4416132.2124472" \
    --form "image_base64=voluptatum" \
    --form "image=@C:\Users\icewa\AppData\Local\Temp\php5180.tmp" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/member_images"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

body.append('member_id', '4416132.2124472');
body.append('image_base64', 'voluptatum');
body.append('image', document.querySelector('input[name="image"]').files[0]);

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());

    'http://api.memberz.test/api/member_images',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',

        ],
        'multipart' => [
            [
                'name' => 'member_id',
                'contents' => '4416132.2124472'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'image_base64',
                'contents' => 'voluptatum'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'image',
                'contents' => fopen('C:\Users\icewa\AppData\Local\Temp\php5180.tmp', 'r')

);

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/members?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/members"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/members',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Query Parameters

Sorting options e.g. ?sort=field1:asc,field2:asc OR ?sort=latest/oldest.

count  integer optional  

Count related models. Alternatively with_count e.g. ?count=relation1,relation2.

contain  string optional  

Contain data from related model e.g. ?contain=relation1,relation2.

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to filter results e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com.

GET api/member_relation_types/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/member_relation_types/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=commodi" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

    "fieldName": "commodi",
};

GET api/member_relations/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/member_relations/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=explicabo" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/member_relations/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "explicabo",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/member_relations/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'explicabo',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

GET api/notifications/unread

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/notifications?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/notifications"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/notifications',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_registration_forms/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=vel" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

Send Message

requires authentication

Adds a message to the queue to dispatch to the phone number

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_registration_forms" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --data "{
    \"organisation_id\": 4609.2923,
    \"organisation_member_category_id\": 5.530296994,
    \"name\": \"sed\",
    \"description\": \"totam\",
    \"expiration_dt\": \"2022-04-12T22:48:18\",
    \"excluded_standard_fields\": \"sit\",
    \"custom_fields\": \"[\\\"quia\\\",\\\"eum\\\"]\",
    \"form_enabled\": true,
    \"deleted_at\": \"2022-04-12T22:48:18\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_registration_forms"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

let body = {
    "organisation_id": 4609.2923,
    "organisation_member_category_id": 5.530296994,
    "name": "sed",
    "description": "totam",
    "expiration_dt": "2022-04-12T22:48:18",
    "excluded_standard_fields": "sit",
    "custom_fields": "[\"quia\",\"eum\"]",
    "form_enabled": true,
    "deleted_at": "2022-04-12T22:48:18"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_accounts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=tempora" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_accounts/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "tempora",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_accounts/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'tempora',
        ],
    ]
);

  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_anniversaries/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=ratione" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_anniversaries/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "ratione",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_anniversaries/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'ratione',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_file_imports/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=ut" \

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

Import File

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_file_imports" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c" \
    --form "organisation_id=6.2807423" \
    --form "import_to_id=70.44900247" \
    --form "import_type=members" \
    --form "import_file=@C:\Users\icewa\AppData\Local\Temp\php5609.tmp" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_file_imports"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('organisation_id', '6.2807423');
body.append('import_to_id', '70.44900247');
body.append('import_type', 'members');
body.append('import_file', document.querySelector('input[name="import_file"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_file_imports',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'multipart/form-data',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'multipart' => [
            [
                'name' => 'organisation_id',
                'contents' => '6.2807423'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_to_id',
                'contents' => '70.44900247'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_type',
                'contents' => 'members'
            ],
            [
                'name' => 'import_file',
                'contents' => fopen('C:\Users\icewa\AppData\Local\Temp\php5609.tmp', 'r')
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_group_leaders/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=reiciendis" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_group_leaders/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "reiciendis",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_group_leaders/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'reiciendis',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_invoice_items/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=sit" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_invoice_items/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "sit",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_invoice_items/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'sit',
        ],

);

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_member_categories/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=tempora" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_member_categories/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "tempora",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_member_categories/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'tempora',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

GET api/organisation_members/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_members/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=sint" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_members/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "sint",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_members/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'sint',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/payment_platforms/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=quisquam" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

    "http://api.memberz.test/api/payment_platforms/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "quisquam",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",

};

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_roles?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_roles"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_roles',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_settings/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=alias" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_settings/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "alias",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisation_settings/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'alias',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

);

    "fieldName": "aut",
};

    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisations/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=ut" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/organisations/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "ut",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/organisations/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'ut',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
