Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/permissions/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=nemo" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/permissions/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "nemo",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/permissions/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'nemo',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

GET api/sms_account_messages/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/sms_account_messages/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=aspernatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/sms_account_messages/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "aspernatur",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/sms_account_messages/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'aspernatur',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search

  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/sms_broadcasts/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=eveniet" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/sms_broadcasts/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "eveniet",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/sms_broadcasts/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'eveniet',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Get All

requires authentication

Returns a list of items in this resource and allows filtering the data based on fields in the database

Options for searching / filtering

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

GET api/subscription_types/count

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/subscription_types/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=tempora" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/subscription_types/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "tempora",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/subscription_types/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'tempora',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/system_setting_category/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=est" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/system_setting_category/search"
);

const params = {
    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "est",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/system_setting_category/search',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'limit'=> '3',
            'page'=> '1',
            'sort'=> 'latest',
            'fieldName'=> 'est',
        ],

);

Query Parameters

fieldName  string optional  

Pass any field and value to search by e.g. name=John&email=any@aol.com. Search logic may use LIKE or = depending on field.

Search Resources

requires authentication

Allows searching for data in this resource using multiple options.

Options for searching

  • By field name: e.g. ?name=John - Specific search
  • By field name with LIKE operator: e.g. ?name_like=John - Fuzzy search
  • By field name with != operator: e.g. ?age_not=5
  • By field name with > or < operator: e.g. ?age_gt=5 or ?age_lt=10
  • By field name with >= or <= operator: e.g. ?age_gte=5 or ?age_lte=10
  • By field name with IN or NOT IN operator: e.g. ?id_in=1,3,5 or ?id_notIn=2,4
  • By field name with NULL or NOT NULL operator: e.g. ?email_isNull or ?email_isNotNull
Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.memberz.test/api/system_settings/search?limit=3&page=1&sort=latest&fieldName=est" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"

    "http://api.memberz.test/api/system_settings/search"
);

    "limit": "3",
    "page": "1",
    "sort": "latest",
    "fieldName": "est",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",

Create a new record of this resource in the database. You can return related data or counts of related data in the response using the count and contain query params

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/transaction_types" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "X-Tenant-ID: 5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.memberz.test/api/transaction_types"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {token}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "X-Tenant-ID": "5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://api.memberz.test/api/transaction_types',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {token}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
            'X-Tenant-ID' => '5b8f3f08-2350-4e38-859e-f5b9af9ce96c',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
